Nat Geo photographer @amivitale found these orphaned baby elephants frolicking in a mud hole at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e) in northern Kenya. Not only is it good fun, but a coating of soil helps protect sensitive elephant skin by acting as both sunscreen and insect repellent.

@r.e.s.c.u.e is the first ever community-owned elephant sanctuary in Africa. This oasis where orphans grow up, learning to be wild so that one day they can rejoin their herds, is a story as much about the elephants as it is about all of humanity.
Follow @amivitale and @r.e.s.c.u.e to learn more, including how to get involved. @conservationorg @kenyawildlifeservice @sandiegozoo @tusk_org @thephotosociety #protectelephants #elephants #stoppoaching #kenya #conservation

